answers.answer: All baby's are different. Your still early so there's gonna be days you'll feel baby more than others. I didn't get daily movements that were noticeable until about 20 weeks. She now moves almost all day and night long. It's like she never sleeps! I'm 25+3 with my second child as well.
Thank you so much I have juvenile diabetes also and I seem to panic I just, thought it was unusual cause I can't see the, baby all the time it is very comforting to hear that I'm not the only one
Try drinking cold orange juice and laying on your left side and maybe baby will move a bit for you. I would get worried too when that would happen but that's what us mom's do right!
